Jishaku.help: Shortcut for 'jsk sh pip'. Invokes the system shell.

Jishaku.name: jishaku hide
Jishaku.help: Hides Jishaku from the help command.

Jishaku.name: jishaku rtt
Jishaku.help: Calculates Round-Trip Time to the API.

Jishaku.name: jishaku dis
Jishaku.help: Disassemble Python code into bytecode.

Jishaku.name: jishaku retain
Jishaku.help:
Turn variable retention for REPL on or off.

Provide no argument for current status.

Jishaku.name: jishaku repeat
Jishaku.help:
Runs a command multiple times in a row.

This acts like the command was invoked several times manually, so it obeys cooldowns.
You can use this in conjunction with `jsk sudo` to bypass this.

Jishaku.name: jishaku load
Jishaku.help:
Loads or reloads the given extension names.

Reports any extensions that failed to load.

Jishaku.name: jishaku curl
Jishaku.help:
Download and display a text file from the internet.

This command is similar to jsk cat, but accepts a URL.

Jishaku.name: jishaku sync
Jishaku.help: Sync global or guild application commands to Discord.

Jishaku.name: jishaku ast
Jishaku.help: Disassemble Python code into AST.

Jishaku.name: jishaku node
Jishaku.help: Shortcut for scaffolding and executing 'npm run'. Only exists if the executables are detected.

Jishaku.name: jishaku tasks
Jishaku.help: Shows the currently running jishaku tasks.

Jishaku.name: jishaku unload
Jishaku.help:
Unloads the given extension names.

Reports any extensions that failed to unload.

Jishaku.name: jishaku debug
Jishaku.help: Run a command timing execution and catching exceptions.

Jishaku.name: jishaku shell
Jishaku.help:
Executes statements in the system shell.

This uses the system shell as defined in $SHELL, or `/bin/bash` otherwise.
Execution can be cancelled by closing the paginator.
